---
// OWNER: Agent 7 (about page).
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const agents = [
  { n: 1, role: "Design system", desc: "global.css and the dark terminal palette" },
  { n: 2, role: "Base layout", desc: "the shell every page renders inside" },
  { n: 3, role: "Chrome", desc: "header, footer, and SEO head" },
  { n: 4, role: "Home page", desc: "the landing grid" },
  { n: 5, role: "Post layout", desc: "how an individual article is framed" },
  { n: 6, role: "Blog index", desc: "the list of everything written" },
  { n: 7, role: "Words", desc: "the posts and this very page" },
  { n: 8, role: "Syndication", desc: "the RSS feed" },
];
---
<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="A meta dev blog built by eight AI subagents in a herdr grid, documenting its own construction."
>
  <article class="about">
    <h1>About this blog</h1>

    <p class="lede">
      This is a dev blog that documents the very demo that built it: eight AI
      subagents, working in parallel, assembling an Astro site about the tools
      they were using to assemble it.
    </p>

    <h2>The herd metaphor</h2>
    <p>
      A <strong>herd</strong> is a group that moves together without a single one
      of them being in charge of the others. That is exactly how this site was
      made. Each agent grazed its own patch — a layout here, a stylesheet there,
      a couple of posts — and the result moved as one. No member needed to watch
      the others; they only needed to head the same direction. The terminal grid
      that held them is named for the idea: <strong>herdr</strong>.
    </p>

    <h2>The tech</h2>
    <ul class="tech">
      <li>
        <span class="k">Astro</span>
        <span>The content-first web framework. Static by default, fast by
        nature — a natural fit for a blog assembled from many small, independent
        pieces.</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="k">herdr</span>
        <span>A terminal multiplexer that tiled eight live shells into one grid,
        so a human could watch the whole herd work at a glance.</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="k">git worktrees</span>
        <span>One repository, eight checked-out branches, eight directories on
        disk. The isolation that let everyone run flat-out without standing on
        each other's files.</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="k">Claude Code</span>
        <span>The agent driving each pane — reading its brief, honoring the shared
        contracts, and writing only the files it owned.</span>
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>The eight agents</h2>
    <p>
      Credit where it's due. This site exists because eight agents each took one
      slice and trusted the rest of the herd with theirs:
    </p>
    <ol class="agents">
      {agents.map((a) => (
        <li>
          <span class="badge">Agent {a.n}</span>
          <span class="agent-role">{a.role}</span>
          <span class="agent-desc">{a.desc}</span>
        </li>
      ))}
    </ol>

    <p class="outro">
      Want the full story? Read <a href="/blog/b-the-demo-that-built-itself">the
      demo that built itself</a>, or the trick behind
      <a href="/blog/b-conflict-free-merges">eight conflict-free merges</a>.
    </p>
  </article>

  <style>
    .about {
      max-width: var(--max-width);
      margin: 0 auto;
      font-family: var(--font-sans);
      color: var(--fg);
      line-height: 1.7;
    }
    .about h1 {
      font-size: 2.4rem;
      letter-spacing: -0.02em;
      margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    }
    .about h2 {
      margin-top: 2.5rem;
      margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
      font-size: 1.4rem;
      color: var(--accent);
    }
    .lede {
      font-size: 1.2rem;
      color: var(--muted);
      border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
      padding-left: 1rem;
    }
    .about a {
      color: var(--accent-2);
      text-decoration: none;
      border-bottom: 1px solid transparent;
      transition: border-color 0.15s ease;
    }
    .about a:hover {
      border-bottom-color: var(--accent-2);
    }
    .tech {
      list-style: none;
      padding: 0;
      display: grid;
      gap: 0.75rem;
    }
    .tech li {
      background: var(--bg-elev);
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: var(--radius);
      padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
      transition: border-color 0.15s ease, transform 0.15s ease;
    }
    .tech li:hover {
      border-color: var(--accent);
      transform: translateY(-2px);
    }
    .tech .k {
      display: block;
      font-family: var(--font-mono);
      color: var(--accent);
      font-weight: 600;
      margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
    }
    .tech li span:last-child {
      color: var(--muted);
    }
    .agents {
      list-style: none;
      padding: 0;
      display: grid;
      gap: 0.5rem;
    }
    .agents li {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: auto 1fr;
      grid-template-areas: "badge role" "badge desc";
      column-gap: 1rem;
      align-items: baseline;
      padding: 0.75rem 0;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    }
    .agents li:last-child {
      border-bottom: none;
    }
    .badge {
      grid-area: badge;
      align-self: center;
      font-family: var(--font-mono);
      font-size: 0.8rem;
      color: var(--accent-2);
      background: var(--bg-elev);
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: var(--radius);
      padding: 0.25rem 0.6rem;
      white-space: nowrap;
    }
    .agent-role {
      grid-area: role;
      font-weight: 600;
    }
    .agent-desc {
      grid-area: desc;
      color: var(--muted);
      font-size: 0.95rem;
    }
    .outro {
      margin-top: 2.5rem;
      padding-top: 1.5rem;
      border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
      color: var(--muted);
    }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
